          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD",
                "UNFLD",
                "DIFFR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measurements  of  alpha  particle",
                " energy spectra were fulfilled at the angles of 45  -",
                " 160 degrees to the direction of bremsstrahlung beam.",
                " The  alpha  particle  yields   at   each   of   used",
                " bremsstrahlung end-point energy were normalized.  By",
                " substracting the alpha particle yields at successive",
                " end-point  energies  from each other and dividing by",
                " corresponding photon  spectrum  difference,  average",
                " cross  sections  over  2  MeV  energy intervals were",
                " obtained by the  photon  difference  technique.  The",
                " energies  of the median points of the alpha particle",
                " distributions of a pure reaction Be-9(g,n)Be-8(E-exc",
                " =  16.6  MeV)  at  each  angle of detection for each",
                " bremsstrahlung end-point energy were  determined  by",
                " kinematic calculations."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The detected  alpha  particles  were  corrected   for",
                " energy  losses  in  the  beryllium target and in the",
                " inert silicon 'windows' of the Si(Li) detectors. The",
                " alpha  particle  energy spectra were then normalized",
                " for geometric efficiency of the detection system and",
                " for photon flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Alpha particles from  the  Be-9(g,n)Be-8  ->  2a  and",
                " Be-9(g,a-0)He-5  were  studied  in the photon energy",
                " region 18 - 26 MeV;  the results yielded a  combined",
                " integrated cross section of 13.1 (2.0) MeV*mb and an",
                " upper limit on the integrated (g,a-0) cross  section",
                " of  4.0  MeV*mb.  these  reactions together with the",
                " Be-9(g,n-1)Be-8 reaction (which  has  an  integrated",
                " cross  section  of  2.4  (0.4) MeV*mb) are the major",
                " reaction  channels   contributing   to   the   total",
                " photoneutron  cross  section  in this energy region.",
                " the  (g,n-1)  reaction  are  consistent   with   the",
                " population of 3/2+ and 5/2+ states of Be-9."
              ]
            }
          ],
